<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640607-55">
               <interp inst="t17640607-55" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640607-55" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640607-55" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640607"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640607-55" type="date" value="17640607"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640607-55-off313-c367" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-defend484 t17640607-55-off313 t17640607-55-verdict317"></join>
         
               <p>381. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640607-55-defend484" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Lyon 
                  <interp inst="t17640607-55-defend484" type="surname" value="Lyon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-defend484" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-defend484" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17640607-55-off313" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-off313" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-off313" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp>
               marrying 
                     
                        <persName id="t17640607-55-victim486" type="victimName">
                           Jane 
                           Lemon 
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim486" type="surname" value="Lemon"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim486" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim486" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , Jan. 19, 1758; and after that, on the <rs id="t17640607-55-cd314" type="crimeDate">28th of Jan. last</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-off313 t17640607-55-cd314"></join>, he married and took to wife 
                     
                        <persName id="t17640607-55-victim488" type="victimName">
                           Anne 
                           Roberts 
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim488" type="surname" value="Roberts"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim488" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640607-55-victim488" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , <rs id="t17640607-55-viclabel315" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-victim488 t17640607-55-viclabel315"></join>, his former wife being then living
            </rs>. *</p>
               <p>Wm. Clime. Mrs. Roberts is sister-in-law to me; she lives at Whitechapel-bars, and <rs id="t17640607-55-viclabel316" type="occupation">keeps a public house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-victim488 t17640607-55-viclabel316"></join>; she is a woman of substance; I went to Portsmouth, in order to examine the register of the prisoner's marriage to 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person489">
                  Jane 
                  Lemon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person489" type="surname" value="Lemon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person489" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person489" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            : this is a true copy of it.</p>
               <p>Q Did you examine it?</p>
               <p>Clime. I did; I examined the register with this, and compared them; it is right: I examined the book with the paper, and then the paper with the book. I examined the register also at Whitechapel church; here is a copy of the register there, in the same manner. The prisoner at the bar came to me, and said he came from Mrs. Roberts; he said, she said she would not marry without she had my consent to marry him. I told him I had nothing to do with it; I told him there were four small children; I was present at the marriage, and saw him married to her at Whitechapel church; they lived together about three weeks afterwards. The marriage bans between 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person490">
                  John 
                  Lyon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person490" type="surname" value="Lyon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person490" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person490" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person491">
                  Jane
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176406070036"></xptr> Lemon<interp inst="t17640607-55-person491" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person491" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were on the 1st, the 8th, and the 15th of January, 1758.</p>
               <p>The copy of the register read to this purport:</p>
               <p>"
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person492">
                  John 
                  Lyon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person492" type="surname" value="Lyon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person492" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person493">
                  Jane 
                  Lemon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person493" type="surname" value="Lemon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person493" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person493" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , both of this parish, were married in this church by banns, this 19th of January, in the year of our Lord 1758, by me, T. Wood."</p>
               <p>The other copy read to this purport:</p>
               <p>"
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person494">
                  John 
                  Lyon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person494" type="surname" value="Lyon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person494" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person494" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of this parish, butcher, and 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person495">
                  Anne 
                  Roberts 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person495" type="surname" value="Roberts"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person495" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person495" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of the same, widow, were married in this church by licence, this 28th day of January, 1764, by me, T. G. Bennet."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640607-55-person496">
                  William 
                  Case 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person496" type="surname" value="Case"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person496" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person496" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at Portsmouth in the year 1758; I remember the prisoner and 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person497">
                  Jane 
                  Lemon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person497" type="surname" value="Lemon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person497" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person497" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were married there about six years ago; I was in the church, and heard the ceremony performed; I was at the wedding dinner; the prisoner was a ship-mate of mine.</p>
               <p>Q. Was it a marriage in the church?</p>
               <p>Case. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640607-55-person498">
                  Thomas 
                  Smith 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person498" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person498" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person498" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was on board the Royal William with the prisoner; it is about 7 years ago.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you see the prisoner married to 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person499">
                  Jane 
                  Lemon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person499" type="surname" value="Lemon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person499" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person499" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ?</p>
               <p>Smith No; but I saw them in bed together; I do not know whether they were married or not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640607-55-person500">
                  John 
                  Gray 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person500" type="surname" value="Gray"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person500" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person500" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Whitechapel church, and saw 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person501">
                  John 
                  Lyon 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person501" type="surname" value="Lyon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person501" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person501" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and Mrs. 
               <persName id="t17640607-55-person502">
                  Anne 
                  Roberts 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person502" type="surname" value="Roberts"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person502" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person502" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             married.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640607-55-person503">
                  Anne 
                  Roberts 
               <interp inst="t17640607-55-person503" type="surname" value="Roberts"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person503" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-person503" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner made his addresses to me about Christmas, and we were married on the 28th of January last, in Whitechapel church.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I married only Anne Roberts.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640607-55-verdict317" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-verdict317" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17640607-55-punish318" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-punish318" type="punishmentCategory" value="miscPunish"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-punish318" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="branding"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-defend484 t17640607-55-punish318"></join>
               B
            </rs>. <rs id="t17640607-55-punish319" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-punish319" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640607-55-punish319" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="newgate"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640607-55-defend484 t17640607-55-punish319"></join>
               Im
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
